5|$|In 1983, Atari {{released}} several computer versions {{under the}} Atarisoft label. All {{of the computer}} ports had the cement factory level, {{while most of the}} console versions did not. None of the home versions of Donkey Kong had all of the intermissions or animations from <b>the</b> <b>arcade</b> game. Some have Donkey Kong {{on the left side of}} the screen in the barrel level (like he is in <b>the</b> <b>arcade</b> game) and others have him on the right side.|$|E
